Note:
Arbitrary-Precision Decimal Floating-Point (per IEEE 754-2008 §3.5 +
§5 generalized to a user-specified significand precision).

This module provides an unbounded-precision sister to Decimal32/64/128.
The representation is identical in spirit to Decimal128 (decimal digits
in a packed buffer, sign, exponent, kind for special values), but the
significand precision is a per-value runtime parameter rather than the
fixed 7/16/34 of the interchange formats.

Use cases (sovereign-scale digital-currency treasury):
    - Treasury balances at planet scale: trillions of base units with
      micro-precision needs ~30+ significant digits (Decimal128 max
      is 34 which is on the edge).
    - Multi-jurisdiction settlement: exact decimal math without binary
      FP rounding artifacts; sovereign-grade durability benefits from
      precision-overhead margins (50-1000 digits).
    - Pi / arbitrary-mathematical constants computed in-spec.

Representation:
    Allocated struct (56 bytes):
        offset 0  : sign           (0 = positive, 1 = negative)
        offset 8  : kind           (0 finite, 1 +Inf, 2 -Inf, 3 qNaN)
        offset 16 : digits_buffer  (pointer to digit buffer; MSD at idx 0)
        offset 24 : digit_count    (number of valid digits, no leading zeros)
        offset 32 : exponent       (unbiased decimal exponent)
        offset 40 : buffer_size    (allocated bytes in digits_buffer)
        offset 48 : rounding_mode  (per-value default rounding direction)

Digit semantics (consistent with decimal_bignum.runa):
    digits_buffer is a byte array where each byte holds one decimal
    digit 0..9 (NOT ASCII). Index 0 is the most-significant digit.

Operations: add, sub, mul, div, sqrt, neg, abs, fma, all with correct
rounding to the precision specified at construction time. Special
values (NaN, ±Inf, ±Zero) propagate per IEEE 754-2008 §6.

The headline correctness test: "0.1 + 0.2 = 0.3" exactly, at any
precision >= 1 digit. This is the canonical decimal-vs-binary FP
test; if it fails, the implementation has a bug.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/numeric/decimal/decimal_bignum.runa" as Bignum
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/numeric/decimal/ieee754_decimal128.runa" as D128
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/numeric/decimal/ieee754_decimal64.runa" as D64

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constants - kind tags
Note: ============================================================================

Constant APD_KIND_FINITE as Integer is 0
Constant APD_KIND_POS_INF as Integer is 1
Constant APD_KIND_NEG_INF as Integer is 2
Constant APD_KIND_QNAN as Integer is 3

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constants - rounding modes (mirror decimal_bignum + extras for §4.3)
Note: ============================================================================

Constant APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN as Integer is 0
Constant APD_ROUND_HALF_UP as Integer is 1
Constant APD_ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO as Integer is 2
Constant APD_ROUND_TOWARD_POS as Integer is 3
Constant APD_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG as Integer is 4
Constant APD_ROUND_HALF_DOWN as Integer is 5
Constant APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO as Integer is 6

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Constants - format styles for arbitrary_decimal_to_string
Note: ============================================================================

Constant APD_FORMAT_PLAIN as Integer is 0
Constant APD_FORMAT_SCIENTIFIC as Integer is 1
Constant APD_FORMAT_ENGINEERING as Integer is 2
Constant APD_FORMAT_FINANCIAL_ACCOUNTING as Integer is 3

Constant APD_UNPACKED_SIZE as Integer is 56

Constant APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION as Integer is 34

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers - struct accessors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_unpacked_create" takes sign as Integer, kind as Integer, digits as Integer, digit_count as Integer, exponent as Integer, buffer_size as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates an ArbitraryDecimal struct. The digit buffer is OWNED by
    the struct from this point on; callers must NOT free it
    independently. arbitrary_decimal_destroy frees both.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Layout.allocate(56) + 7 stores.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single struct allocation per value.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    On allocation failure we free the supplied digit buffer to avoid a
    double-ownership leak.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let p be Layout.allocate(APD_UNPACKED_SIZE)
    If p is equal to 0:
        If digits is not equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    __store(p, 0, sign)
    __store(p, 8, kind)
    __store(p, 16, digits)
    __store(p, 24, digit_count)
    __store(p, 32, exponent)
    __store(p, 40, buffer_size)
    __store(p, 48, rounding_mode)
    Return p
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_sign" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Sign accessor for the unpacked struct.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Null returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 0)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_kind" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Kind accessor (FINITE, POS_INF, NEG_INF, QNAN).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 8.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Null returns QNAN sentinel.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return APD_KIND_QNAN
    End If
    Return __load(p, 8)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_digits" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Raw digit buffer pointer accessor (one byte per digit, MSD first).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 16.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller MUST NOT free; the struct owns this buffer.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 16)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_digit_count" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Significant-digit count accessor.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 24.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Null returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 24)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_exponent" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Unbiased decimal exponent accessor.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 32.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Null returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 32)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_buffer_size" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocated bytes in the digit buffer (precision capacity hint).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 40.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Null returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return __load(p, 40)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_get_rounding_mode" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Default rounding-mode accessor (per IEEE 754-2008 §4.3).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 48.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Null returns HALF_EVEN.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    Return __load(p, 48)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_set_rounding_mode" takes value as Integer, mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Mutator for the per-value default rounding mode, used by subsequent
    arithmetic when no explicit rounding-mode parameter is passed.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Validate mode; store at offset 48.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Invalid modes are coerced to HALF_EVEN.
    @End Security_Scope

    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let m be mode
    If m is less than 0:
        Set m to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If m is greater than APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Set m to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    __store(value, 48, m)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_destroy" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Frees both the unpacked struct and its owned digit buffer per the
    ownership contract documented in apd_unpacked_create.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Load digit pointer, free it, free struct.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus the deallocator costs.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Double-free triggers the allocator canary protocol.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let d be __load(p, 16)
    If d is not equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(d)
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(p)
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers - rounding-mode translation to decbn
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_rounding_to_decbn" takes mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Maps the APD rounding-mode constants to the matching decimal_bignum
    constants. For modes that decbn does not natively support (HALF_DOWN,
    HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO) we emit a special sentinel handled by
    apd_round_to_precision directly.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Direct table.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) constant fold.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Out-of-range yields HALF_EVEN.
    @End Security_Scope

    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_HALF_UP:
        Return 1
    End If
    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_TOWARD_ZERO:
        Return 2
    End If
    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_TOWARD_POS:
        Return 3
    End If
    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG:
        Return 4
    End If
    Note: HALF_DOWN and HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO map to bignum HALF_EVEN/HALF_UP
    Note: as a base; apd_round_to_precision applies the corrective tweak.
    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_HALF_DOWN:
        Return 0
    End If
    If mode is equal to APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers - rounding (extends decbn with extra modes)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_round_to_precision" takes digits as Integer, count as Integer, precision as Integer, sign as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer, exp_delta_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Rounds a digit buffer to at most 'precision' digits using the APD
    rounding-mode set. For the modes natively supported by decbn we
    delegate; for HALF_DOWN and HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO we implement
    directly with the same rounding-digit/sticky-bit analysis as
    decbn_round_to_precision (per IEEE 754-2008 §4.3.3).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. If precision >= count, return a fresh copy with exp_delta = 0.
    2. For HALF_DOWN: round-half-up's complement (ties go toward zero).
    3. For HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO: ties always increment magnitude.
    4. All other modes: delegate to decbn_round_to_precision.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(count) in the worst case.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0; out pointers set to 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If digits is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is less than or equal to precision:
        If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Let cp be Bignum.decbn_copy(digits, count)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, count)
        End If
        Return cp
    End If

    Note: HALF_DOWN: rounds half-toward-zero. We can implement as half-up
    Note: but if the discarded portion is *exactly* 5000... (rounding
    Note: digit == 5, sticky == 0), we do NOT round up.
    If rounding_mode is equal to APD_ROUND_HALF_DOWN:
        Note: Inspect rounding digit + sticky bit.
        Let rd be Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, precision)
        Let sticky be 0
        Let s be precision plus 1
        While s is less than count:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, s) is not equal to 0:
                Set sticky to 1
                Set s to count
            Otherwise:
                Set s to s plus 1
            End If
        End While
        Note: HALF_DOWN: > 5 rounds away from zero; == 5 with sticky rounds away; == 5 exact rounds toward zero; < 5 rounds toward zero.
        If rd is equal to 5:
            If sticky is equal to 0:
                Note: Exactly 0.5 - round toward zero (truncate).
                Let truncated be Bignum.decbn_copy(digits, precision)
                If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    __store(out_count_ptr, 0, precision)
                End If
                If exp_delta_ptr is not equal to 0:
                    __store(exp_delta_ptr, 0, count minus precision)
                End If
                Return truncated
            End If
        End If
        Note: All other HALF_DOWN cases match HALF_UP. Fall through.
    End If

    Note: HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO: ties go away from zero always. This is the
    Note: same as HALF_UP since HALF_UP also ties away from zero per IEEE
    Note: 754. Falls through to decbn delegation.

    Let bignum_mode be apd_rounding_to_decbn(rounding_mode)
    Return Bignum.decbn_round_to_precision(digits, count, precision, sign, bignum_mode, out_count_ptr, exp_delta_ptr)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers - normalize (strip leading zeros)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_normalize_digits" takes digits as Integer, digit_count as Integer, out_count_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns a fresh digit buffer with leading zeros stripped. If the
    input is all zeros, returns a single-digit zero buffer with count = 1.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Find first non-zero index; copy from there. Identical strategy to
    dec128_normalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If digits is equal to 0:
        Let z be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If z is equal to 0:
            If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
                __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(z, 0, 0)
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 1)
        End If
        Return z
    End If
    Let first_nz be 0
    Let scanning be 1
    While scanning is equal to 1:
        If first_nz is greater than or equal to digit_count minus 1:
            Set scanning to 0
        Otherwise:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, first_nz) is equal to 0:
                Set first_nz to first_nz plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let new_count be digit_count minus first_nz
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(new_count plus 1)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
            __store(out_count_ptr, 0, 0)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than new_count:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, i, Memory.memory_get_byte(digits, first_nz plus i))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If out_count_ptr is not equal to 0:
        __store(out_count_ptr, 0, new_count)
    End If
    Return buf
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers - finalize a finite result (round + wrap struct)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_finalize_finite" takes sign as Integer, digits as Integer, digit_count as Integer, exp as Integer, precision as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Brings a finite digit buffer into the specified precision window
    (IEEE 754-2008 §4.3 directed-rounding). This function OWNS the
    supplied digit buffer and either consumes it or returns a fresh
    rounded copy (in which case the original is freed).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Treat the all-zero case as canonical zero.
    2. Normalize (strip leading zeros).
    3. apd_round_to_precision.
    4. Wrap as an unpacked struct preserving the per-value precision +
       rounding mode.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count) for normalization plus O(excess) for rounding.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failures yield qNaN.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let s be sign
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    Let prec be precision
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to 1
    End If

    If digits is equal to 0:
        Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb is equal to 0:
            Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(s, APD_KIND_FINITE, zb, 1, exp, 2, rounding_mode)
    End If

    Let norm_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If norm_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
    End If
    Let norm_digits be apd_normalize_digits(digits, digit_count, norm_count_ptr)
    Let norm_count be __load(norm_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(norm_count_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(digits)
    If norm_digits is equal to 0:
        Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
    End If

    Note: Detect zero (all-zero buffer).
    Let is_zero be 1
    Let scan_i be 0
    While scan_i is less than norm_count:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(norm_digits, scan_i) is not equal to 0:
            Set is_zero to 0
            Set scan_i to norm_count
        Otherwise:
            Set scan_i to scan_i plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If is_zero is equal to 1:
        Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
        Let zb2 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb2 is equal to 0:
            Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb2, 0, 0)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(s, APD_KIND_FINITE, zb2, 1, exp, 2, rounding_mode)
    End If

    Let rounded_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    Let exp_delta_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If rounded_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
    End If
    If exp_delta_ptr is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(rounded_count_ptr)
        Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
    End If

    Let rounded be apd_round_to_precision(norm_digits, norm_count, prec, s, rounding_mode, rounded_count_ptr, exp_delta_ptr)
    Let rounded_count be __load(rounded_count_ptr, 0)
    Let exp_delta be __load(exp_delta_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(rounded_count_ptr)
    Layout.deallocate(exp_delta_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(norm_digits)
    If rounded is equal to 0:
        Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
    End If

    Let final_exp be exp plus exp_delta
    Return apd_unpacked_create(s, APD_KIND_FINITE, rounded, rounded_count, final_exp, rounded_count plus 2, rounding_mode)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Internal helpers - NaN/Inf propagation
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_propagate_nan" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008 §6.2 NaN propagation: any qNaN operand produces
    a qNaN result. We inherit the precision/rounding from the first
    NaN operand.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Check a then b; allocate a qNaN with the inherited precision hint.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is not equal to 0:
        If __load(a, 8) is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
            Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, __load(a, 48))
        End If
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        If __load(b, 8) is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
            Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, __load(b, 48))
        End If
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Special-value constructors
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_make_zero" takes sign as Integer, precision_digits as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed zero with preferred exponent 0 (per IEEE 754-2008 §3.3
    canonical zero) and the specified precision capacity.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate a single-digit buffer holding 0; wrap.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Two allocations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Sign normalized to 0/1.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let s be sign
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(prec plus 4)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(buf, 0, 0)
    Return apd_unpacked_create(s, APD_KIND_FINITE, buf, 1, 0, prec plus 4, rounding_mode)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity" takes sign as Integer, precision_digits as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed infinity (per IEEE 754-2008 §3.3).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    No digit buffer; tag with POS_INF or NEG_INF.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One struct allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Sign normalized to 0/1.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let s be sign
    If s is not equal to 0:
        Set s to 1
    End If
    Let k be APD_KIND_POS_INF
    If s is equal to 1:
        Set k to APD_KIND_NEG_INF
    End If
    Return apd_unpacked_create(s, k, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan" takes precision_digits as Integer, rounding_mode as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Quiet NaN (per IEEE 754-2008 §6.2). Per spec, NaN sign bit is
    payload, not numerical; we set it to 0.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    No digit buffer.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One struct allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return apd_unpacked_create(0, APD_KIND_QNAN, 0, 0, 0, 0, rounding_mode)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Predicates
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_is_zero" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    True iff finite and all coefficient digits are zero.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Kind check + buffer scan.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count) worst case.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 8) is not equal to APD_KIND_FINITE:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let dc be __load(p, 24)
    If dc is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let d be __load(p, 16)
    If d is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than dc:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(d, i) is not equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_is_finite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008: finite iff not NaN and not Inf.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Kind compare.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 8) is equal to APD_KIND_FINITE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_is_infinite" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    True for +Inf or -Inf.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Kind compare.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let k be __load(p, 8)
    If k is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    If k is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_is_nan" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    True for quiet NaN.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Kind compare.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 8) is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_is_negative" takes p as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    True iff sign bit is set. Does NOT consider magnitude (so -0 returns 1).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Load offset 0.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Pure.
    @End Security_Scope

    If p is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If __load(p, 0) is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Construction - from Integer
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_from_integer" takes value as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Exact conversion of an Integer to an ArbitraryDecimal. Integer is
    at most 18 decimal digits in the bootstrap stage1, which fits in
    any precision >= 18 without rounding. For lower precisions we
    delegate to apd_finalize_finite which applies HALF_EVEN rounding
    per IEEE 754-2008 §4.3.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Sign extraction; digit-buffer build via decbn_from_integer; wrap.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log10 |value|).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure aside from allocations.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If
    Let sign be 0
    Let mag be value
    If mag is less than 0:
        Set sign to 1
        Set mag to 0 minus mag
    End If
    If mag is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_zero(0, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let cnt_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If cnt_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_from_integer(mag, cnt_ptr)
    Let cnt be __load(cnt_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(cnt_ptr)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Return apd_finalize_finite(sign, buf, cnt, 0, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Construction - from string (IEEE 754-2008 §5.12.2)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_from_string" takes s as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parses a null-terminated ASCII decimal string per IEEE 754-2008
    §5.12.2. Accepts forms:
        [+|-] digits [. digits] [ (e|E) [+|-] digits ]
        [+|-] Inf | Infinity | NaN
    The parsed coefficient is built with unbounded digit count, then
    rounded to precision_digits via apd_finalize_finite.

    Headline correctness: arbitrary_decimal_from_string("0.1") +
    arbitrary_decimal_from_string("0.2") = arbitrary_decimal_from_string("0.3")
    exactly at any precision >= 1.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single-pass scan with explicit state (saw_dot, frac_digits,
    leading_zero). Coefficient digits accumulate into a buffer sized
    proportional to input. Exponent parsed separately. Final
    exponent = explicit_exp - frac_digits.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single pass over input; allocation cost proportional to digit count.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Malformed input produces qNaN. Buffer overflows during accumulation
    are not possible because we size the digit buffer based on the
    string length.
    @End Security_Scope

    If s is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(precision_digits, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If

    Note: First pass: measure the string length to size the digit buffer.
    Let slen be 0
    Let lp be 0
    Let scanning_len be 1
    While scanning_len is equal to 1:
        Let lb be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, lp)
        If lb is equal to 0:
            Set scanning_len to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set slen to slen plus 1
            Set lp to lp plus 1
            If slen is greater than 1048576:
                Set scanning_len to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Let pos be 0
    Note: Skip leading whitespace.
    Let scanning_ws be 1
    While scanning_ws is equal to 1:
        Let bws be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
        If bws is equal to 32:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If bws is equal to 9:
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            Otherwise:
                If bws is equal to 10:
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    If bws is equal to 13:
                        Set pos to pos plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set scanning_ws to 0
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Note: Sign.
    Let sign be 0
    Let bsign be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    If bsign is equal to 45:
        Set sign to 1
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If bsign is equal to 43:
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If

    Note: Inf / Infinity.
    Let bi1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    Let bi2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 1)
    Let bi3 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 2)
    Let is_inf be 0
    If bi1 is equal to 73:
        If bi2 is equal to 110:
            If bi3 is equal to 102:
                Set is_inf to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If bi1 is equal to 105:
        If bi2 is equal to 110:
            If bi3 is equal to 102:
                Set is_inf to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If is_inf is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(sign, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Note: NaN.
    Let bn1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    Let bn2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 1)
    Let bn3 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos plus 2)
    Let is_nan be 0
    If bn1 is equal to 78:
        If bn2 is equal to 97:
            If bn3 is equal to 78:
                Set is_nan to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If bn1 is equal to 110:
        If bn2 is equal to 97:
            If bn3 is equal to 110:
                Set is_nan to 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If is_nan is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Note: Coefficient parsing. Buffer sized to slen + 4 (worst-case all
    Note: digits, no whitespace, no sign, no dot).
    Let digit_cap be slen plus 4
    If digit_cap is less than 16:
        Set digit_cap to 16
    End If
    Let digit_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(digit_cap)
    If digit_buf is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let dc be 0
    Let leading_zero be 1
    Let frac_digits be 0
    Let saw_dot be 0
    Let saw_digit be 0
    Let scanning be 1

    While scanning is equal to 1:
        Let bd be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
        If bd is equal to 46:
            If saw_dot is equal to 1:
                Set scanning to 0
            Otherwise:
                Set saw_dot to 1
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If bd is greater than or equal to 48:
                If bd is less than or equal to 57:
                    Let dv be bd minus 48
                    If leading_zero is equal to 1:
                        If dv is not equal to 0:
                            If dc is less than digit_cap:
                                Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, dc, dv)
                                Set dc to dc plus 1
                            End If
                            Set leading_zero to 0
                        End If
                    Otherwise:
                        If dc is less than digit_cap:
                            Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, dc, dv)
                            Set dc to dc plus 1
                        End If
                    End If
                    If saw_dot is equal to 1:
                        Set frac_digits to frac_digits plus 1
                    End If
                    Set saw_digit to 1
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set scanning to 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning to 0
            End If
        End If
    End While

    If saw_digit is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(digit_buf)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If dc is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, 0, 0)
        Set dc to 1
    End If

    Note: Exponent.
    Let exp_val be 0
    Let bexp be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
    Let exp_marker_seen be 0
    If bexp is equal to 101:
        Set exp_marker_seen to 1
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If bexp is equal to 69:
        Set exp_marker_seen to 1
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If exp_marker_seen is equal to 1:
        Let exp_sign be 0
        Let bs2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
        If bs2 is equal to 45:
            Set exp_sign to 1
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        If bs2 is equal to 43:
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        Let scanning_exp be 1
        While scanning_exp is equal to 1:
            Let be2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(s, pos)
            If be2 is greater than or equal to 48:
                If be2 is less than or equal to 57:
                    Set exp_val to (exp_val multiplied by 10) plus (be2 minus 48)
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set scanning_exp to 0
                End If
            Otherwise:
                Set scanning_exp to 0
            End If
        End While
        If exp_sign is equal to 1:
            Set exp_val to 0 minus exp_val
        End If
    End If

    Let final_exp be exp_val minus frac_digits
    Return apd_finalize_finite(sign, digit_buf, dc, final_exp, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Construction - from Decimal128 / Decimal64
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_from_decimal128" takes value as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Lossless widening from Decimal128. Decimal128's 34-digit significand
    fits in any precision >= 34 without rounding; for lower precisions
    HALF_EVEN rounding applies per IEEE 754-2008 §4.3.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Copy kind, sign, exponent, and digit buffer; delegate to
    apd_finalize_finite to apply precision-cap rounding.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(34) digit copy.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NaN / Inf inputs preserved.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to 34
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let kind128 be __load(value, 8)
    If kind128 is equal to 3:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If kind128 is equal to 4:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let s be __load(value, 0)
    If kind128 is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(0, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If kind128 is equal to 2:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(1, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let d128 be __load(value, 16)
    Let dc128 be __load(value, 24)
    Let e128 be __load(value, 32)
    If d128 is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_zero(s, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_copy(d128, dc128)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Return apd_finalize_finite(s, buf, dc128, e128, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_from_decimal64" takes value as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Lossless widening from Decimal64. Decimal64 stores its coefficient
    as a single Integer (<=16 digits). We convert to digit-buffer
    representation via decbn_from_integer then delegate to
    apd_finalize_finite.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Read coefficient as Integer; decompose into digit buffer.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log10 coefficient).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NaN / Inf inputs preserved.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to 16
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let kind64 be __load(value, 8)
    If kind64 is equal to 3:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If kind64 is equal to 4:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let s be __load(value, 0)
    If kind64 is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(0, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If kind64 is equal to 2:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(1, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let coeff be __load(value, 16)
    Let e64 be __load(value, 24)
    If coeff is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_zero(s, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let cnt_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If cnt_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let buf be Bignum.decbn_from_integer(coeff, cnt_ptr)
    Let cnt be __load(cnt_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(cnt_ptr)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Return apd_finalize_finite(s, buf, cnt, e64, prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comparison
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_compare" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Three-way compare returning -1, 0, +1, or -2 (NaN unordered).
    Implements IEEE 754-2008 §5.6.1 compareSignalingTotalOrder
    minus the totalOrder tiebreak (which we do not need; equality is
    sufficient for arithmetic dispatch).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN -> -2 unordered.
    2. Inf handling (POS > finite > NEG; +Inf = +Inf; -Inf = -Inf).
    3. Sign handling (-x < +y for any x,y>0).
    4. Same-sign: align exponents to the smaller value, compare
       magnitudes in the digit-buffer domain.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Best case O(1) for sign-differing operands; worst case O(digit
    count + |exp diff|).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns -2 (sentinel matches NaN unordered).
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return -2
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return -2
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Return -2
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Return -2
    End If

    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return -1
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return -1
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)

    Let a_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(b)
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If

    If sa is not equal to sb:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            If b_zero is equal to 1:
                Return 0
            End If
        End If
        If sa is equal to 1:
            Return -1
        End If
        Return 1
    End If

    Note: Same sign: align both digit buffers to the smaller exponent.
    Let exp_common be ea
    If eb is less than ea:
        Set exp_common to eb
    End If
    Let shift_a be ea minus exp_common
    Let shift_b be eb minus exp_common

    Let scaled_a_count be dca plus shift_a
    Let scaled_b_count be dcb plus shift_b
    Let scaled_a be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_a_count plus 1)
    If scaled_a is equal to 0:
        Return -2
    End If
    Let scaled_b be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_b_count plus 1)
    If scaled_b is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
        Return -2
    End If

    Let ai be 0
    While ai is less than dca:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, ai, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, ai))
        Set ai to ai plus 1
    End While
    Let az be 0
    While az is less than shift_a:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, dca plus az, 0)
        Set az to az plus 1
    End While

    Let bi be 0
    While bi is less than dcb:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, bi, Memory.memory_get_byte(db, bi))
        Set bi to bi plus 1
    End While
    Let bz be 0
    While bz is less than shift_b:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, dcb plus bz, 0)
        Set bz to bz plus 1
    End While

    Let cmp be Bignum.decbn_compare_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Return 0 minus cmp
    End If
    Return cmp
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_eq" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008 §5.11 compareQuietEqual: NaN != anything.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Wraps arbitrary_decimal_compare with the NaN-unordered guard.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Comparable to arbitrary_decimal_compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    NaN inputs always return 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be arbitrary_decimal_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_ne" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Logical negation of arbitrary_decimal_eq. Per IEEE 754-2008
    §5.11 NaN comparisons are always 'not equal'.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Inverts the equal flag; NaN -> ne returns 1 (matching IEEE).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Comparable to arbitrary_decimal_compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    NaN inputs always return 1.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be arbitrary_decimal_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_lt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008 §5.11 compareQuietLess.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Three-way compare == -1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Comparable to arbitrary_decimal_compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    NaN -> 0 (unordered).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be arbitrary_decimal_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_le" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008 §5.11 compareQuietLessEqual.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Three-way compare in {-1, 0}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Comparable to arbitrary_decimal_compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    NaN -> 0 (unordered).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be arbitrary_decimal_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to -1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_gt" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008 §5.11 compareQuietGreater.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Three-way compare == 1.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Comparable to arbitrary_decimal_compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    NaN -> 0 (unordered).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be arbitrary_decimal_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_ge" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Per IEEE 754-2008 §5.11 compareQuietGreaterEqual.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Three-way compare in {0, 1}.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Comparable to arbitrary_decimal_compare.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    NaN -> 0 (unordered).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let c be arbitrary_decimal_compare(a, b)
    If c is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Negation, abs
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_neg" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bit-level sign flip with NaN/Inf preserved. Per IEEE 754-2008 §5.5.1
    negate(NaN) -> NaN; negate(+Inf) -> -Inf and vice versa.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Copy digit buffer; flip sign and kind for infinities; preserve
    precision and rounding mode.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One digit-buffer copy plus one struct allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure aside from allocations.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let bs be __load(a, 40)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)

    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(bs, rm)
    End If
    Let new_sign be 1
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Set new_sign to 0
    End If
    Let new_kind be ka
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set new_kind to APD_KIND_NEG_INF
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set new_kind to APD_KIND_POS_INF
    End If
    Let copy_digits be 0
    If da is not equal to 0:
        Set copy_digits to Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
        If copy_digits is equal to 0:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(bs, rm)
        End If
    End If
    Return apd_unpacked_create(new_sign, new_kind, copy_digits, dca, ea, bs, rm)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_abs" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Absolute value: clear sign bit, preserve everything else. Per IEEE
    754-2008 §5.5.1 abs(NaN) -> NaN; abs(-Inf) -> +Inf.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Copy digit buffer; set sign to 0; map NEG_INF -> POS_INF.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One digit-buffer copy plus one struct allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure aside from allocations.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let bs be __load(a, 40)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(bs, rm)
    End If
    Let new_kind be ka
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set new_kind to APD_KIND_POS_INF
    End If
    Let copy_digits be 0
    If da is not equal to 0:
        Set copy_digits to Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
        If copy_digits is equal to 0:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(bs, rm)
        End If
    End If
    Return apd_unpacked_create(0, new_kind, copy_digits, dca, ea, bs, rm)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Addition / subtraction
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Arbitrary-precision decimal addition per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1. The
    inputs may carry different per-value precisions; the result uses
    the precision specified in the precision_digits argument (the
    caller dictates the answer's precision; this is the IEEE
    convention for the "preferredWidth" attribute).

    Headline test: arbitrary_decimal_from_string("0.1") +
    arbitrary_decimal_from_string("0.2") = arbitrary_decimal_from_string("0.3")
    must hold exactly at any precision >= 1.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN propagation, Inf handling (+Inf + -Inf -> qNaN invalid).
    2. Align both operands to the smaller exponent by zero-padding the
       higher-exponent operand's digit buffer.
    3. Same sign -> decbn_add_magnitude; else compare magnitudes,
       decbn_sub_magnitude, sign of result = sign of larger operand.
    4. apd_finalize_finite to round to precision.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Alignment can scale up to precision + 2 digits in pathological cases.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Inf + (-Inf) signals invalid -> qNaN.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If
    Let np be apd_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np is not equal to 0:
        Return np
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)
    If rm is less than 0:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If rm is greater than APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If

    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(0, prec, rm)
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(1, prec, rm)
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(0, prec, rm)
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(1, prec, rm)
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)

    Note: Align both operands to a single exp_common per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1.
    Note: Natural choice is min(ea, eb), but the larger-magnitude operand
    Note: would then require scaling UP by (max - min) digits. To bound
    Note: the alignment buffer size we cap the upward scale at cap_shift =
    Note: prec + 4 digits (the +4 supplies 4 extra digits of working
    Note: precision beyond the final round window). When the exponent
    Note: gap exceeds cap_shift, exp_common is re-anchored UP to
    Note: max(ea, eb) - cap_shift; the larger operand then scales UP by
    Note: exactly cap_shift digits and the smaller operand scales DOWN
    Note: by (gap - cap_shift) digits, with any non-zero discarded
    Note: digit recorded as combined_sticky. Both scaled buffers share
    Note: a common LSB-extension digit (value = combined_sticky on the
    Note: smaller-magnitude operand, 0 on the other; result_exp shifts
    Note: down by 1) so decbn_add_magnitude / decbn_sub_magnitude (which
    Note: right-justify operands) see the sticky bit as a proper digit
    Note: of the sum and the subsequent apd_round_to_precision applies
    Note: round-half-even (and the other IEEE 754 modes) correctly.
    Let cap_shift be prec plus 4
    Let max_exp be ea
    If eb is greater than ea:
        Set max_exp to eb
    End If
    Let min_exp be eb
    If ea is less than eb:
        Set min_exp to ea
    End If
    Let exp_common be min_exp
    If (max_exp minus min_exp) is greater than cap_shift:
        Set exp_common to max_exp minus cap_shift
    End If

    Let shift_a be ea minus exp_common
    Let shift_b be eb minus exp_common

    Note: Compute the down-shift amount for each operand (digits dropped
    Note: from the LSB end of the buffer in MSB-first storage). At most
    Note: one of down_a/down_b is non-zero since exp_common is anchored
    Note: to one operand's exponent.
    Let down_a be 0
    If shift_a is less than 0:
        Set down_a to 0 minus shift_a
        Set shift_a to 0
    End If
    Let down_b be 0
    If shift_b is less than 0:
        Set down_b to 0 minus shift_b
        Set shift_b to 0
    End If

    Note: kept_X = digits retained from operand X. Any non-zero digit in
    Note: positions [kept_X .. dcX - 1] (LSB-end discards) sets sticky_X.
    Let kept_a be dca minus down_a
    If kept_a is less than 0:
        Set kept_a to 0
    End If
    Let kept_b be dcb minus down_b
    If kept_b is less than 0:
        Set kept_b to 0
    End If

    Let sticky_a be 0
    If down_a is greater than 0:
        Let scan_a be kept_a
        Let scan_a_done be 0
        While scan_a_done is equal to 0:
            If scan_a is greater than or equal to dca:
                Set scan_a_done to 1
            Otherwise:
                If Memory.memory_get_byte(da, scan_a) is not equal to 0:
                    Set sticky_a to 1
                    Set scan_a_done to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set scan_a to scan_a plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If
    Let sticky_b be 0
    If down_b is greater than 0:
        Let scan_b be kept_b
        Let scan_b_done be 0
        While scan_b_done is equal to 0:
            If scan_b is greater than or equal to dcb:
                Set scan_b_done to 1
            Otherwise:
                If Memory.memory_get_byte(db, scan_b) is not equal to 0:
                    Set sticky_b to 1
                    Set scan_b_done to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Set scan_b to scan_b plus 1
                End If
            End If
        End While
    End If

    Note: combined_sticky = sticky from EITHER operand. If either operand
    Note: dropped non-zero LSB digits, append a shared LSB digit to BOTH
    Note: scaled buffers (value = the operand's own sticky bit so the
    Note: digit-place is preserved) and decrement exp_common by 1 so the
    Note: result exponent matches the new combined-buffer LSB position.
    Let combined_sticky be sticky_a bitwise or sticky_b
    Let sticky_pad be combined_sticky
    If sticky_pad is not equal to 0:
        Set exp_common to exp_common minus 1
    End If

    Let scaled_a_count be kept_a plus shift_a plus sticky_pad
    Let scaled_b_count be kept_b plus shift_b plus sticky_pad
    If scaled_a_count is less than 1:
        Set scaled_a_count to 1
    End If
    If scaled_b_count is less than 1:
        Set scaled_b_count to 1
    End If

    Let scaled_a be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_a_count plus 1)
    If scaled_a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    Let scaled_b be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_b_count plus 1)
    If scaled_b is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Note: scaled_a layout (MSB-first):
    Note: [da[0]..da[kept_a-1]] [0..0 x shift_a] [sticky_a if sticky_pad else nothing]
    Let ai be 0
    While ai is less than kept_a:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, ai, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, ai))
        Set ai to ai plus 1
    End While
    Let az be 0
    While az is less than shift_a:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, kept_a plus az, 0)
        Set az to az plus 1
    End While
    If sticky_pad is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, kept_a plus shift_a, sticky_a)
    End If
    If (kept_a plus shift_a plus sticky_pad) is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_a, 0, 0)
    End If

    Let bi be 0
    While bi is less than kept_b:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, bi, Memory.memory_get_byte(db, bi))
        Set bi to bi plus 1
    End While
    Let bz be 0
    While bz is less than shift_b:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, kept_b plus bz, 0)
        Set bz to bz plus 1
    End While
    If sticky_pad is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, kept_b plus shift_b, sticky_b)
    End If
    If (kept_b plus shift_b plus sticky_pad) is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled_b, 0, 0)
    End If

    Let result_sign be 0
    Let combined_buf be 0
    Let combined_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If combined_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    If sa is equal to sb:
        Set combined_buf to Bignum.decbn_add_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count, combined_count_ptr)
        Set result_sign to sa
    Otherwise:
        Let cmp be Bignum.decbn_compare_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count)
        If cmp is greater than 0:
            Set combined_buf to Bignum.decbn_sub_magnitude(scaled_a, scaled_a_count, scaled_b, scaled_b_count, combined_count_ptr)
            Set result_sign to sa
        End If
        If cmp is less than 0:
            Set combined_buf to Bignum.decbn_sub_magnitude(scaled_b, scaled_b_count, scaled_a, scaled_a_count, combined_count_ptr)
            Set result_sign to sb
        End If
        If cmp is equal to 0:
            Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
            If zb is equal to 0:
                Layout.deallocate(combined_count_ptr)
                Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
                Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)
                Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
            Set combined_buf to zb
            __store(combined_count_ptr, 0, 1)
            If rm is equal to APD_ROUND_TOWARD_NEG:
                Set result_sign to 1
            Otherwise:
                Set result_sign to 0
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let combined_count be __load(combined_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(combined_count_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_a)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled_b)

    If combined_buf is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Return apd_finalize_finite(result_sign, combined_buf, combined_count, exp_common, prec, rm)
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_sub" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Subtraction is defined per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1 as a + (-b).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compose neg then add.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One extra struct allocation versus a direct subtract.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Same NaN/Inf semantics as add.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let neg_b be arbitrary_decimal_neg(b)
    If neg_b is equal to 0:
        Let prec be precision_digits
        If prec is less than 1:
            Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let result be arbitrary_decimal_add(a, neg_b, precision_digits)
    arbitrary_decimal_destroy(neg_b)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Multiplication
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_mul" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Arbitrary-precision decimal multiplication per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1.
    The intermediate product can have up to dca + dcb digits, which is
    held exactly in a digit buffer and then rounded to precision_digits.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN propagation, Inf handling (Inf * 0 -> qNaN invalid).
    2. Compute coefficient product via decbn_mul.
    3. Add exponents.
    4. apd_finalize_finite.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(dca * dcb) with the classical schoolbook algorithm in decbn_mul.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure -> qNaN.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If
    Let np be apd_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np is not equal to 0:
        Return np
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)
    If rm is less than 0:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If rm is greater than APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If

    Let result_sign be 0
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        Set result_sign to 1
    End If

    Let a_inf be 0
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    Let b_inf be 0
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If

    Let a_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(b)

    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If

    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)
    Let exp_sum be ea plus eb

    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_zero(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_zero(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If

    Let prod_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If prod_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    Let prod be Bignum.decbn_mul(da, dca, db, dcb, prod_count_ptr)
    Let prod_count be __load(prod_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(prod_count_ptr)
    If prod is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Return apd_finalize_finite(result_sign, prod, prod_count, exp_sum, prec, rm)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Division
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_div" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Arbitrary-precision decimal division per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1. We
    pre-scale the dividend by 10^(precision+1) digits so that the
    integer quotient carries (precision + 1) decimal digits, then use
    sticky-bit injection to preserve rounding-decision information
    discarded by the long-division floor.

    For 1/7 to 100 digits this produces "0.142857142857..." with the
    period-6 repeating sequence. For 1/3 to 1000 digits all digits are 3.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN/Inf/zero special cases.
    2. Append (precision + 1) zero digits to dividend's buffer.
    3. decbn_div_mod.
    4. Sticky-bit OR into quotient's last digit if remainder is non-zero.
    5. apd_finalize_finite.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O((precision+1) * dcb * 10) for the schoolbook long division.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    0 / 0 -> qNaN; x / 0 (x != 0) -> signed infinity (divideByZero
    signal per IEEE 754-2008 §7.3).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If
    Let np be apd_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np is not equal to 0:
        Return np
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)
    If rm is less than 0:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If rm is greater than APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If

    Let result_sign be 0
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        Set result_sign to 1
    End If

    Let a_inf be 0
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    Let b_inf be 0
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If

    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_inf is equal to 1:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_zero(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If

    Let a_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(b)
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(result_sign, prec, rm)
    End If
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Let ea0 be __load(a, 32)
        Let eb0 be __load(b, 32)
        Let zero_exp be ea0 minus eb0
        Let zb0 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(prec plus 4)
        If zb0 is equal to 0:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb0, 0, 0)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(result_sign, APD_KIND_FINITE, zb0, 1, zero_exp, prec plus 4, rm)
    End If

    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)

    Let guard_digits be prec plus 1
    Let scaled_count be dca plus guard_digits
    Let scaled be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_count plus 1)
    If scaled is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    Let si be 0
    While si is less than dca:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled, si, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, si))
        Set si to si plus 1
    End While
    Let zi be 0
    While zi is less than guard_digits:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(scaled, dca plus zi, 0)
        Set zi to zi plus 1
    End While

    Let q_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    Let r_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    Let r_out_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If q_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    If r_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    If r_out_ptr is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
        Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    __store(r_out_ptr, 0, 0)

    Let q_buf be Bignum.decbn_div_mod(scaled, scaled_count, db, dcb, q_count_ptr, r_count_ptr, r_out_ptr)
    Let q_count be __load(q_count_ptr, 0)
    Let r_count be __load(r_count_ptr, 0)
    Let rem_buf be __load(r_out_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
    Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
    Layout.deallocate(r_out_ptr)
    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
    If q_buf is equal to 0:
        If rem_buf is not equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(rem_buf)
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Note: Sticky bit: if any remainder digit is non-zero we have lost
    Note: precision; OR a +1 into the quotient's last digit if it is even
    Note: (Knuth TAOCP Vol 2 §4.3 sticky-injection idiom).
    Let rem_nonzero be 0
    Let rni be 0
    While rni is less than r_count:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(rem_buf, rni) is not equal to 0:
            Set rem_nonzero to 1
            Set rni to r_count
        Otherwise:
            Set rni to rni plus 1
        End If
    End While
    If rem_buf is not equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(rem_buf)
    End If
    If rem_nonzero is equal to 1:
        Let last_q be Memory.memory_get_byte(q_buf, q_count minus 1)
        If last_q is equal to ((last_q divided by 2) multiplied by 2):
            Memory.memory_set_byte(q_buf, q_count minus 1, last_q plus 1)
        End If
    End If

    Let final_exp be ea minus eb minus guard_digits
    Return apd_finalize_finite(result_sign, q_buf, q_count, final_exp, prec, rm)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Square root
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_sqrt" takes a as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Arbitrary-precision sqrt per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1. We scale the
    coefficient up to >= 2 * precision_digits with an even exponent,
    then run Newton iteration in the digit-buffer domain.

    Negative input is invalid -> qNaN.
    sqrt(+Inf) = +Inf; sqrt(+0) = +0; sqrt(-0) = -0; sqrt(NaN) = NaN.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Sign/NaN/Inf/zero special cases.
    2. Scale up to >= 2 * precision digits via zero-pad with even exp.
    3. Newton: x_new = (x + scaled / x) / 2, monotonic-decrease term.
    4. Halve exponent.
    5. apd_finalize_finite.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Converges in ~log2(precision) iterations. Each iteration is a
    long-division (the dominant cost).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Negative -> qNaN with invalid signal per §7.2.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)
    If rm is less than 0:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If rm is greater than APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)

    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(0, prec, rm)
    End If

    If arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(a) is equal to 1:
        Let zb be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
        If zb is equal to 0:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zb, 0, 0)
        Return apd_unpacked_create(sa, APD_KIND_FINITE, zb, 1, ea divided by 2, 2, rm)
    End If

    If sa is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Note: Scale up to >= 2 * precision digits.
    Let target_digits be prec multiplied by 2
    Let scaled_count be dca
    Let scaled_exp be ea
    Let scaled be Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
    If scaled is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    While scaled_count is less than target_digits:
        Let bigger_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_count plus 3)
        If bigger_buf is equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Let cpi be 0
        While cpi is less than scaled_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf, cpi, Memory.memory_get_byte(scaled, cpi))
            Set cpi to cpi plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf, scaled_count, 0)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf, scaled_count plus 1, 0)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Set scaled to bigger_buf
        Set scaled_count to scaled_count plus 2
        Set scaled_exp to scaled_exp minus 2
    End While

    Note: Ensure exponent is even.
    If scaled_exp minus ((scaled_exp divided by 2) multiplied by 2) is not equal to 0:
        Let bigger_buf2 be Bignum.decbn_alloc(scaled_count plus 2)
        If bigger_buf2 is equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Let cpi2 be 0
        While cpi2 is less than scaled_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf2, cpi2, Memory.memory_get_byte(scaled, cpi2))
            Set cpi2 to cpi2 plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_byte(bigger_buf2, scaled_count, 0)
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Set scaled to bigger_buf2
        Set scaled_count to scaled_count plus 1
        Set scaled_exp to scaled_exp minus 1
    End If

    Note: Initial guess: 10^((d/2)-1) (1 followed by (d/2)-1 zeros).
    Let guess_count be scaled_count divided by 2
    If guess_count is less than 1:
        Set guess_count to 1
    End If
    Let guess be Bignum.decbn_alloc(guess_count plus 2)
    If guess is equal to 0:
        Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(guess, 0, 1)
    Let gi be 1
    While gi is less than guess_count:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(guess, gi, 0)
        Set gi to gi plus 1
    End While

    Note: Newton iteration: x_new = (x + scaled / x) / 2 with monotonic-
    Note: decrease termination. Cap iterations defensively.
    Let iter be 0
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If iter is greater than 200:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let q_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
            Let r_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
            Let r_out_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
            If q_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                Set done to 1
                Set iter to 999
            Otherwise:
                If r_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                    Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
                    Set done to 1
                    Set iter to 999
                Otherwise:
                    If r_out_ptr is equal to 0:
                        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
                        Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
                        Set done to 1
                        Set iter to 999
                    Otherwise:
                        __store(r_out_ptr, 0, 0)
                        Let div_quot be Bignum.decbn_div_mod(scaled, scaled_count, guess, guess_count, q_count_ptr, r_count_ptr, r_out_ptr)
                        Let dq_count be __load(q_count_ptr, 0)
                        Let dr_buf be __load(r_out_ptr, 0)
                        Layout.deallocate(q_count_ptr)
                        Layout.deallocate(r_count_ptr)
                        Layout.deallocate(r_out_ptr)
                        If dr_buf is not equal to 0:
                            Bignum.decbn_free(dr_buf)
                        End If
                        If div_quot is equal to 0:
                            Set done to 1
                        Otherwise:
                            Let add_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                            If add_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                                Bignum.decbn_free(div_quot)
                                Set done to 1
                            Otherwise:
                                Let sum be Bignum.decbn_add_magnitude(guess, guess_count, div_quot, dq_count, add_count_ptr)
                                Let sum_count be __load(add_count_ptr, 0)
                                Layout.deallocate(add_count_ptr)
                                Bignum.decbn_free(div_quot)
                                If sum is equal to 0:
                                    Set done to 1
                                Otherwise:
                                    Let two_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(2)
                                    If two_buf is equal to 0:
                                        Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                        Set done to 1
                                    Otherwise:
                                        Memory.memory_set_byte(two_buf, 0, 2)
                                        Let nq_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                                        Let nr_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                                        Let nr_out_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
                                        If nq_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                                            Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                            Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                            Set done to 1
                                        Otherwise:
                                            If nr_count_ptr is equal to 0:
                                                Layout.deallocate(nq_count_ptr)
                                                Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                                Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                                Set done to 1
                                            Otherwise:
                                                If nr_out_ptr is equal to 0:
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nq_count_ptr)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nr_count_ptr)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                                    Set done to 1
                                                Otherwise:
                                                    __store(nr_out_ptr, 0, 0)
                                                    Let new_guess be Bignum.decbn_div_mod(sum, sum_count, two_buf, 1, nq_count_ptr, nr_count_ptr, nr_out_ptr)
                                                    Let ng_count be __load(nq_count_ptr, 0)
                                                    Let nr_buf be __load(nr_out_ptr, 0)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nq_count_ptr)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nr_count_ptr)
                                                    Layout.deallocate(nr_out_ptr)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(sum)
                                                    Bignum.decbn_free(two_buf)
                                                    If nr_buf is not equal to 0:
                                                        Bignum.decbn_free(nr_buf)
                                                    End If
                                                    If new_guess is equal to 0:
                                                        Set done to 1
                                                    Otherwise:
                                                        Let cmp_ng be Bignum.decbn_compare_magnitude(new_guess, ng_count, guess, guess_count)
                                                        If cmp_ng is greater than or equal to 0:
                                                            Bignum.decbn_free(new_guess)
                                                            Set done to 1
                                                        Otherwise:
                                                            Bignum.decbn_free(guess)
                                                            Set guess to new_guess
                                                            Set guess_count to ng_count
                                                            Set iter to iter plus 1
                                                        End If
                                                    End If
                                                End If
                                            End If
                                        End If
                                    End If
                                End If
                            End If
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End While

    Bignum.decbn_free(scaled)
    Let result_exp be scaled_exp divided by 2
    Return apd_finalize_finite(0, guess, guess_count, result_exp, prec, rm)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Fused multiply-add
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_fma" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, c as Integer, precision_digits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Fused multiply-add per IEEE 754-2008 §5.4.1: (a * b) + c with a
    SINGLE correctly-rounded result. The exact product is computed in
    the digit-buffer domain (up to dca+dcb digits, unbounded by
    precision_digits) and then added to c with the user's rounding
    mode. The "single rounding" property holds because the intermediate
    product is exact in the buffer representation; only the final
    add+round step introduces rounding.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. NaN propagation across all three operands.
    2. Inf handling: Inf*0 + anything -> qNaN; otherwise propagate Inf.
    3. Compute exact product (no precision cap).
    4. Wrap as an unpacked struct with sufficient precision capacity
       to hold the full product.
    5. arbitrary_decimal_add with the user's rounding mode and
       precision_digits.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    One large mul + one add. Heavier than separate mul+add by ~25%
    but produces the IEEE 754-2008 correctly-rounded result.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Inf * 0 + anything -> qNaN; Inf*finite + opposite-sign-Inf -> qNaN.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let prec be precision_digits
    If prec is less than 1:
        Set prec to APD_DEFAULT_PRECISION
    End If
    Let np_ab be apd_propagate_nan(a, b)
    If np_ab is not equal to 0:
        Return np_ab
    End If
    Let np_c be apd_propagate_nan(c, c)
    If np_c is not equal to 0:
        Return np_c
    End If
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If
    If c is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN)
    End If

    Let ka be __load(a, 8)
    Let kb be __load(b, 8)
    Let kc be __load(c, 8)
    Let sa be __load(a, 0)
    Let sb be __load(b, 0)
    Let sc be __load(c, 0)
    Let rm be __load(a, 48)
    If rm is less than 0:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If
    If rm is greater than APD_ROUND_HALF_AWAY_FROM_ZERO:
        Set rm to APD_ROUND_HALF_EVEN
    End If

    Let sign_p be 0
    If sa is not equal to sb:
        Set sign_p to 1
    End If

    Let a_inf be 0
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set a_inf to 1
    End If
    Let b_inf be 0
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    If kb is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set b_inf to 1
    End If
    Let c_inf be 0
    If kc is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Set c_inf to 1
    End If
    If kc is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Set c_inf to 1
    End If

    Let a_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be arbitrary_decimal_is_zero(b)

    Let prod_is_inf be 0
    If a_inf is equal to 1:
        If b_zero is equal to 1:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Set prod_is_inf to 1
    End If
    If b_inf is equal to 1:
        If a_zero is equal to 1:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Set prod_is_inf to 1
    End If

    If prod_is_inf is equal to 1:
        If c_inf is equal to 1:
            If sc is not equal to sign_p:
                Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
            End If
        End If
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(sign_p, prec, rm)
    End If
    If c_inf is equal to 1:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_infinity(sc, prec, rm)
    End If

    Note: All finite. Compute exact product, wrap, then add c.
    Let da be __load(a, 16)
    Let db be __load(b, 16)
    Let dca be __load(a, 24)
    Let dcb be __load(b, 24)
    Let ea be __load(a, 32)
    Let eb be __load(b, 32)
    Let exp_sum be ea plus eb

    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Let copy_c be arbitrary_decimal_neg(c)
        If copy_c is equal to 0:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Let restored be arbitrary_decimal_neg(copy_c)
        arbitrary_decimal_destroy(copy_c)
        Return restored
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Let copy_c2 be arbitrary_decimal_neg(c)
        If copy_c2 is equal to 0:
            Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
        End If
        Let restored2 be arbitrary_decimal_neg(copy_c2)
        arbitrary_decimal_destroy(copy_c2)
        Return restored2
    End If

    Let prod_count_ptr be Layout.allocate(8)
    If prod_count_ptr is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If
    Let prod be Bignum.decbn_mul(da, dca, db, dcb, prod_count_ptr)
    Let prod_count be __load(prod_count_ptr, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(prod_count_ptr)
    If prod is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Let exact_prod be apd_unpacked_create(sign_p, APD_KIND_FINITE, prod, prod_count, exp_sum, prod_count plus 2, rm)
    If exact_prod is equal to 0:
        Return arbitrary_decimal_make_qnan(prec, rm)
    End If

    Let result be arbitrary_decimal_add(exact_prod, c, prec)
    arbitrary_decimal_destroy(exact_prod)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: String formatting (IEEE 754-2008 §5.12.2 + financial extensions)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "apd_count_int_digits" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Counts decimal digits in a non-negative Integer. Used by the
    exponent formatter.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Successive division by 10.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(log10 value).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Negative input treated as absolute value.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let v be value
    If v is less than 0:
        Set v to 0 minus v
    End If
    If v is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let n be 0
    While v is greater than 0:
        Set n to n plus 1
        Set v to v divided by 10
    End While
    Return n
End Process

Process called "apd_write_int" takes value as Integer, out as Integer, offset as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes a signed Integer as ASCII into out starting at offset.
    Returns the number of bytes written.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Sign byte (if negative), then digits from MSD to LSD via reverse.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    O(log10 |value|).
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Caller must ensure adequate buffer capacity (at most 20 bytes for
    signed 64-bit Integer).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let cur be offset
    Let v be value
    If v is less than 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, cur, 45)
        Set cur to cur plus 1
        Set v to 0 minus v
    End If
    If v is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, cur, 48)
        Return cur plus 1 minus offset
    End If
    Let tmp be Layout.allocate(24)
    If tmp is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tp be 0
    While v is greater than 0:
        Let dd be v minus ((v divided by 10) multiplied by 10)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(tmp, tp, dd plus 48)
        Set tp to tp plus 1
        Set v to v divided by 10
    End While
    Let mi be tp minus 1
    While mi is greater than or equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, cur, Memory.memory_get_byte(tmp, mi))
        Set cur to cur plus 1
        Set mi to mi minus 1
    End While
    Layout.deallocate(tmp)
    Return cur minus offset
End Process

Process called "apd_write_plain" takes p as Integer, out as Integer, out_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Plain decimal formatting: "[-]ddd.ddd" with no exponent suffix.
    Handles arbitrary exponent positions including those where leading
    zeros must be inserted ("0.000123") or trailing zeros appended
    ("12300000").
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Sign byte.
    2. If exponent >= 0: emit digits, then |exp| trailing zeros.
    3. If exponent < 0: with k = -exp digit positions after the point,
       emit either "0.000...digits" (when k > digit_count) or insert
       the dot at position digit_count - k.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count + |exp|).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Insufficient output buffer returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sa be __load(p, 0)
    Let da be __load(p, 16)
    Let dca be __load(p, 24)
    Let ea be __load(p, 32)
    Let pos be 0
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 45)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If

    If ea is greater than or equal to 0:
        Note: Emit digits then trailing zeros.
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than dca:
            If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, i) plus 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Let z be 0
        While z is less than ea:
            If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set z to z plus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Let neg_e be 0 minus ea
        If neg_e is greater than or equal to dca:
            Note: "0.000...digits"
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 46)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Let lz be 0
            While lz is less than neg_e minus dca:
                If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                    Return 0
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                Set lz to lz plus 1
            End While
            Let i2 be 0
            While i2 is less than dca:
                If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                    Return 0
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, i2) plus 48)
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                Set i2 to i2 plus 1
            End While
        Otherwise:
            Note: Dot at position dca - neg_e.
            Let dot_pos be dca minus neg_e
            Let i3 be 0
            While i3 is less than dca:
                If i3 is equal to dot_pos:
                    If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                        Return 0
                    End If
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 46)
                    Set pos to pos plus 1
                End If
                If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                    Return 0
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, i3) plus 48)
                Set pos to pos plus 1
                Set i3 to i3 plus 1
            End While
        End If
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
    Return pos
End Process

Process called "apd_write_scientific" takes p as Integer, out as Integer, out_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Scientific notation: "[-]D.DDDeEXP" with the implicit dot after the
    first significant digit. Matches IEEE 754-2008 §5.12.2's expressed
    decimal form.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Sign byte.
    2. First digit + "." + remaining digits (skip dot if dca == 1).
    3. "e" + signed exponent of the form (ea + dca - 1).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Insufficient buffer returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sa be __load(p, 0)
    Let da be __load(p, 16)
    Let dca be __load(p, 24)
    Let ea be __load(p, 32)
    Let pos be 0
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 45)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If dca is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 101)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
        Return pos
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, 0) plus 48)
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    If dca is greater than 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 46)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Let k be 1
        While k is less than dca:
            If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, k) plus 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set k to k plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 101)
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let exp_eff be ea plus dca minus 1
    Let wrote be apd_write_int(exp_eff, out, pos)
    Set pos to pos plus wrote
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
    Return pos
End Process

Process called "apd_write_engineering" takes p as Integer, out as Integer, out_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Engineering notation: like scientific, but the exponent is constrained
    to a multiple of 3 and the mantissa has 1-3 digits before the dot.
    Used in scientific/engineering display where SI-prefix alignment is
    expected.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Compute effective exponent E = ea + dca - 1.
    2. Find E_eng = floor(E / 3) * 3 (handling negatives: -1/3 = -1 in
       floor semantics, but integer division truncates toward zero; we
       adjust for negatives explicitly).
    3. Mantissa shift = E - E_eng (in {0, 1, 2}); the mantissa has
       (1 + shift) digits before the dot.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Insufficient buffer returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sa be __load(p, 0)
    Let da be __load(p, 16)
    Let dca be __load(p, 24)
    Let ea be __load(p, 32)
    Let pos be 0
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 45)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    If dca is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 101)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
        Return pos
    End If

    Let E be ea plus dca minus 1
    Let E_eng be 0
    Let shift be 0
    Note: floor(E / 3) toward negative infinity.
    If E is greater than or equal to 0:
        Set E_eng to (E divided by 3) multiplied by 3
        Set shift to E minus E_eng
    Otherwise:
        Note: For negative E, integer division truncates toward zero. To
        Note: get floor, subtract 2 (or up to 2) from E before dividing.
        Let neg_E be 0 minus E
        Let mod3 be neg_E minus ((neg_E divided by 3) multiplied by 3)
        If mod3 is equal to 0:
            Set E_eng to E
            Set shift to 0
        Otherwise:
            Set E_eng to E minus (3 minus mod3)
            Set shift to 3 minus mod3
        End If
    End If

    Let mant_int_digits be shift plus 1
    Note: Emit mantissa: mant_int_digits before dot, then dot then remaining.
    Let k be 0
    While k is less than dca:
        If k is equal to mant_int_digits:
            If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 46)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(da, k) plus 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set k to k plus 1
    End While
    If dca is less than mant_int_digits:
        Let trz be dca
        While trz is less than mant_int_digits:
            If pos is greater than or equal to out_size minus 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, out_size minus 1, 0)
                Return 0
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set trz to trz plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 101)
    Set pos to pos plus 1
    Let wrote be apd_write_int(E_eng, out, pos)
    Set pos to pos plus wrote
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
    Return pos
End Process

Process called "apd_write_financial" takes p as Integer, out as Integer, out_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Financial-accounting format: fixed two decimal places (cent
    precision), parentheses for negative numbers per US GAAP financial
    statement convention. The value is conceptually rounded to two
    decimal places for display but the underlying ArbitraryDecimal is
    not mutated.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    1. Make a working copy of the digit buffer.
    2. Adjust to exponent -2 by either appending zeros (exp > -2),
       round-half-even truncation (exp < -2), or no change.
    3. Emit "(...)" if negative, otherwise emit plain digits with the
       dot two positions from the right.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count + |exp + 2|).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Insufficient buffer returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let sa be __load(p, 0)
    Let da be __load(p, 16)
    Let dca be __load(p, 24)
    Let ea be __load(p, 32)
    Note: Build a working buffer scaled to exponent -2.
    Let target_exp be -2
    Let work_count be dca
    Let work_buf be Bignum.decbn_copy(da, dca)
    If work_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If ea is greater than target_exp:
        Note: Append (ea - target_exp) trailing zeros.
        Let add_z be ea minus target_exp
        Let big_buf be Bignum.decbn_alloc(work_count plus add_z plus 2)
        If big_buf is equal to 0:
            Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
            Return 0
        End If
        Let cpi be 0
        While cpi is less than work_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(big_buf, cpi, Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, cpi))
            Set cpi to cpi plus 1
        End While
        Let zi be 0
        While zi is less than add_z:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(big_buf, work_count plus zi, 0)
            Set zi to zi plus 1
        End While
        Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
        Set work_buf to big_buf
        Set work_count to work_count plus add_z
    End If
    If ea is less than target_exp:
        Note: Round-half-even truncate (target_exp - ea) digits.
        Let drop be target_exp minus ea
        If drop is greater than or equal to work_count:
            Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
            Let pos2 be 0
            If sa is equal to 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 40)
                Set pos2 to pos2 plus 1
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 48)
            Set pos2 to pos2 plus 1
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 46)
            Set pos2 to pos2 plus 1
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 48)
            Set pos2 to pos2 plus 1
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 48)
            Set pos2 to pos2 plus 1
            If sa is equal to 1:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 41)
                Set pos2 to pos2 plus 1
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos2, 0)
            Return pos2
        End If
        Let kept be work_count minus drop
        Let rd be Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, kept)
        Let sticky be 0
        Let si be kept plus 1
        While si is less than work_count:
            If Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, si) is not equal to 0:
                Set sticky to 1
                Set si to work_count
            Otherwise:
                Set si to si plus 1
            End If
        End While
        Let rup be 0
        If rd is greater than 5:
            Set rup to 1
        Otherwise:
            If rd is equal to 5:
                If sticky is equal to 1:
                    Set rup to 1
                Otherwise:
                    If kept is greater than 0:
                        Let lk be Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, kept minus 1)
                        If lk is not equal to ((lk divided by 2) multiplied by 2):
                            Set rup to 1
                        End If
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
        Set work_count to kept
        If rup is equal to 1:
            Let carry be 1
            Let cp be work_count minus 1
            While cp is greater than or equal to 0:
                If carry is equal to 0:
                    Set cp to -1
                Otherwise:
                    Let d2 be Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, cp)
                    Set d2 to d2 plus 1
                    If d2 is equal to 10:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, cp, 0)
                        Set carry to 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, cp, d2)
                        Set carry to 0
                    End If
                    Set cp to cp minus 1
                End If
            End While
            If carry is equal to 1:
                Let r2 be work_count minus 1
                While r2 is greater than or equal to 0:
                    Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, r2 plus 1, Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, r2))
                    Set r2 to r2 minus 1
                End While
                Memory.memory_set_byte(work_buf, 0, 1)
                Set work_count to work_count plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Let pos be 0
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 40)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    Note: Emit with dot at position work_count - 2.
    If work_count is less than 3:
        Note: Pad with leading zero(s) to ensure at least "0.dd".
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 46)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        If work_count is equal to 1:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        End If
        Let kk be 0
        While kk is less than work_count:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, kk) plus 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set kk to kk plus 1
        End While
    Otherwise:
        Let dot_pos be work_count minus 2
        Let kk2 be 0
        While kk2 is less than work_count:
            If kk2 is equal to dot_pos:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 46)
                Set pos to pos plus 1
            End If
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, Memory.memory_get_byte(work_buf, kk2) plus 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set kk2 to kk2 plus 1
        End While
    End If
    Bignum.decbn_free(work_buf)
    If sa is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 41)
        Set pos to pos plus 1
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
    Return pos
End Process

Process called "arbitrary_decimal_to_string" takes value as Integer, buffer as Integer, buffer_size as Integer, format_style as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multi-style decimal formatter per IEEE 754-2008 §5.12.2 plus
    accounting-style extensions. Selects between plain, scientific,
    engineering, and financial outputs.

    Special values: NaN -> "NaN", +Inf -> "Inf", -Inf -> "-Inf".
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Dispatch on format_style with shared NaN/Inf handling.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(digit_count) plus the style-specific overhead.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Insufficient buffer returns 0 with no partial writes guaranteed.
    Callers must provide buffer_size >= digit_count + 32 for safety.
    @End Security_Scope

    If buffer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If buffer_size is less than 8:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 97)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 0)
        Return 3
    End If

    Let ka be __load(value, 8)
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_QNAN:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 97)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 78)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 0)
        Return 3
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_POS_INF:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 73)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 110)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 102)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 0)
        Return 3
    End If
    If ka is equal to APD_KIND_NEG_INF:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 0, 45)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 1, 73)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 2, 110)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 3, 102)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(buffer, 4, 0)
        Return 4
    End If

    If format_style is equal to APD_FORMAT_SCIENTIFIC:
        Return apd_write_scientific(value, buffer, buffer_size)
    End If
    If format_style is equal to APD_FORMAT_ENGINEERING:
        Return apd_write_engineering(value, buffer, buffer_size)
    End If
    If format_style is equal to APD_FORMAT_FINANCIAL_ACCOUNTING:
        Return apd_write_financial(value, buffer, buffer_size)
    End If
    Return apd_write_plain(value, buffer, buffer_size)
End Process
